text: Josephine Cook née Page, second marriage Josephine Honnor, (born 1931), is a female former athlete who competed for England. ==Athletics career== She represented England in the shot put at the 1958 British Empire and Commonwealth Games in Cardiff, Wales. ==References== Category:1931 births Category:English female shot putters Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 1958 British Empire and Commonwealth Games Category:Living people
title: Josephine Cook
